column2: Overcast- heavy rain 24 hours before- and there is no algae bloom in the lake.
Sunny and no algae in the water.
Weather clear- no rain for threes days- no algae- no duckweed on surface- and light wind.
Light wind- sunny- no algae- spots of submerging weeds- no rain for 8 days- and there are spots of duckweed.
No wind- rained 18 hours before reading- no algae- spots of submerging weeds- and duckweed in channel that feeds from Dell Creek.
It has been 48 hours after rain- light wind- sunny- no algae- spots of submerging weeds- and duckweeds in channel near Dell Creek.
No rain for 24 hours- wind calm- no algae- little duckweed- and the lake was sprayed for duckweed 5 days before.
North wind at 40 mph with rain 24 hours before today- calm- sunny- duckweed- and there is no algae.
Calm- rain 24 hours before- no algae- duckweed- submerging weeds
No rain 5 days before today- light wind- weed cutting and harvesting 48 hours before now- weed spraying 72 hours before now- submerging weeds- duck weed- suds floating on top of water
Light wind- rained for days- lots of duckweed- no algae- bright sunshine- light motorboat traffic for past 5-6 days.
Rain 8 days - heavy winds- and a sea of duckweed during this period- today light wind- no algae- sunny- lots of ducks along shoreline
Light wind- cloudy- no duckweed- no algae- submerging weeds- last reading of the year.
No wind- sunshine- snow ice still on.
Windy- 75 degrees- no algae- no duckweed- bright sunshine.  Rain for 48 hours before reading.
Light wind- sunshine- duckweed present- air temp 72.
Windy- sunny- rain for 4 days- no algae- duckweed- air temp 74- lake 6" higher than usual
Duckweed present- windy- sunshine- rain 48 hours before reading- no algae- air temp 81
Sunshine- little wind- no rain for 4 days- moderate amount of duckweed- no algae- air temp 82
Duckweed present- bright sunshine- rain 24 hours before- air temp 84
Cloudy- rain night before- light wind.  No algae.  80 degrees- lots of duckweed- mouth of dell creek.
Cloudy- very calm- rain for 3 days- no algae- 50 degrees.
Cloudy- no wind- small amount of duckweed- 40 degrees- lots of rain.
Cloudy- light wind- rain in the morning- 50 degrees- last reading of the year.
Too cold to swim.  65 degrees- little duck weed- submergent weed floating- very messy in spots- bright sunshine- light wind.
Public perception due to duck weed.  Sunshine- light wind- 85 degrees- rain 48 before duckweed harvesting- no algae.
Public perception due to duck weed.  Sunny- slight wind- 84 degrees.  5" rain last 48 hours.  Lots of duck weed.  No algae.
Public perception due to duck weed.  Sunny- light wind- 80 degrees.  Lots of rain last week- lots of duckweed.
Public perception due to duck weed.  Light wind- cloudy- 84 degrees- no algae- no rain 5 days.
Windy- 60 degrees- lots of rain last month.  Last reading this year.
Air temp 71 F.  Sunny.  No rain.
Sunny- no wind.  Lots of duckweed.  Air temp 86.2 F.
Overcast- air 60 F.  Windy.  Lots of ducks - different kinds.
Sunny- slight wind.  Colors changing.  Air 80 F.

column1: Can see debris still attached to tree branches indicating how high the water
level was.  Not a lot of duck weed.  Saw lots of pine needles floaoting on surface.
Saw dredging machine on big lake.  Rather windy - partly cloudy
Lots of trees down - Water level very high
Still see mud and effect of high water on tree leaves

column2: Ambient temp. - 83 deg. - partly cloudy and very humid

column1: Rained last night - see more duck weed
FIRST READING AFTER MAJOR FLOODING + HIGH WATER

column2: Collected samples as training session group (CLMN training) with members of the lake association and district. Collected for phosphorous. Weather: partly sunny- wind 15 mph. Saw many bird species- including vulture peeking out of a cave nesting site.
Weather clear and sunny with light wind.
Weather sunny and clear with a 10 mph wind.
Sunny - Light breeze- 80 degrees- spotty clouds- Saw bald eagle west end of lake. Worked With Katrina Punzel.
Sunny- SW breeze- 75 degrees- Spotty clouds. Worked with my grandson Daniel Zeier and Jeanne Scherer DNR
Weather was cloudy- 37 degrees- NE wind 5-10- snow showers. My wife Sandy helped me.
Weather was clear and sunny- wind was SE at 5 to10- temp. was 75 degrees.
Mostly sunny- wind 5-10- temp 70. Large pine tree removed from channel west of Fern Dell today
